Write the isClosed method in the Loop class.
Remember to respond with a snippet in the form of the following:
```
class Loop {
    isClosed() {
        // your code here
    }
}
```

```javascript
class Loop {
    isClosed() {
        if (!this.edges || this.edges.length < 2) {
            return false;
        }
        const firstVertex = this.edges[0].startVertex;
        const lastVertex = this.edges[this.edges.length - 1].endVertex;
        return firstVertex.equals(lastVertex);
    }
}
```
